The paper focuses on named entity recognition (NER) from clinical notes, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural architectures and transfer learning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of parameter sharing and optimization, which are also relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
